   Horsham Board Increase
</HL>
<DATE>
08/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   HSM T.HSM WNEWS
</CO>
<LP>
   TORONTO -- Horsham Corp. said it increased the size of its
board to 12 members, from eight, and elected a fifth new
member to succeed a retiring director.
   Horsham said David Beck and James Tory, both Toronto
lawyers; David Gilmour, vice chairman of New York-based
Arlington Investments Ltd.; Robert Helman, a Chicago lawyer;
and Duke Ligon of Bankers Trust Co., New York, were elected
to its board.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company said Samuel Zell, chairman of Chicago-based
Equity Financial &amp; Management Co., retired from the board.
   Horsham, an investment and oil and gas concern, said it
had been operating with "a relatively small board," and
decided to increase the number of directors to strengthen the
board.
