   International Brief -- Cadbury Schweppes PLC:
   Pretax Profit Increased 12%
   In 1st Half at British Firm
</HL>
<DATE>
08/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CADBY
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Cadbury Schweppes PLC, a British beverages and sweets
manufacturer, reported a 12% rise in pretax profit on the
back of strong earnings in Europe which were partially offset
by a sharp rise in interest charges.
   Pretax profit for the six months to June 16 rose to 105
million pounds ($204 million) from 93.9 million pounds.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Cadbury said U.K and overseas properties acquired in the
last year are making "satisfactory progress" and contributed
to the gain in earnings.
   Group sales jumped 22% to 1.41 billion pounds from 1.15
billion pounds, including record sales of 640 million pounds
in the U.K., up from 506 million pounds last year.
</TEXT>
