<HL>
   Shell Oil Wins Jet Fuel Contract
</HL>
<DATE>
08/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2
</SO>
<CO>
   RD SC ALD WX TXN
</CO>
<IN>
OIL, INTEGRATED MAJORS (OIL)
PETROLEUM (PET)
AEROSPACE (ARO)
</IN>
<GV>
DEFENSE DEPARTMENT (DEF)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- The Defense Logistics Agency awarded jet
fuel contracts to Shell Oil Co., unit of Royal Dutch/Shell
Group, for $135.3 million; Fina Oil &amp; Chemical Co. for $41.9
million; Wyoming Refining Co. for $25.1 million; and Sinclair
Oil Corp. for $10.1 million.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   Allied-Signal Inc. was issued a $20.7 million Air Force
contract for aircraft parts.
                                                                                                       

   Westinghouse Electric Corp. received a $16.4 million Air
