</IN>
<LP>
   Perkin-Elmer Corp. reported a 3% increase in net income
for the fourth quarter ending July 31 as sales rose 7.4%,
reflecting successful restructuring efforts completed during
fiscal 1990.
   Perkin-Elmer, which manufactures analytical instruments
used in material-science laboratories, reported quarterly net
income rose to $13.6 million, or 38 cents a share, from $13.2
million, or 30 cents a share, in the year-earlier period.
Per-share earnings reflect the company's buy-back of 10.1
million of its common shares.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In addition to the share buy-back, the restructuring
included the sale of seven business units by the Norwalk,
Conn., company.
   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,
Perkin-Elmer shares closed at $22.875, up $1.375.
